<p><cs><col><b>Ancon sheep</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a breed of
sheep with short crooked legs and long back. It originated in
Massachusetts in 1791; -- called also the <altname>otter
breed</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
